uk.gov.nationalarchives.droid.binFileReader
Class AbstractByteReader

java.lang.Object
  uk.gov.nationalarchives.droid.binFileReader.AbstractByteReader
All Implemented Interfaces:
ByteReader
Direct Known Subclasses:
FileByteReader, StreamByteReader
public abstract class AbstractByteReader
extends Object
implements ByteReader

Abstract base class for the ByteReader interface.

This implements the methods that are passed on to the IdentificationFile object.

linb

newByteReader

public static ByteReader newByteReader(IdentificationFile theIDFile,
                                       boolean readFile)
Static constructor for a ByteReader object, and depending on the readFile setting, it may or may not read in the binary file specified.

This may create a FileByteReader, UrlByteReader or InputStreamByteReader, depending on the the nature of the IdentificationFile passed in.

Parameters:
theIDFile - The file to be read in
readFile - Flag specifying whether file should be read in or not
Returns:

newByteReader

public static ByteReader newByteReader(IdentificationFile theIDFile,
                                       InputStream inputStream)
Static constructor for a ByteReader object, and depending on the readFile setting, it may or may not read in the binary file specified.

This will create InputStreamByteReader, if the FilePath of the IdentificationFile has been set to "-"; otherwise it will invoke the DROID static method newByteReader(theIDFile) It will read the underlying InputStream

Parameters:
theIDFile - The file to be read in
inputStream - InputStream to be turned into an InputStreamByteReader and read
Returns:
